There will always been successful "calls". The question is whether directional call buying, on a steady diet, is a profitable endeavour. Answer: It is not.
I criticize by category not individual, Pat.
The academic report says that sometimes unusual activity brings non public information. I have written alot about that - its simpley not, in the main, true.

The performance of unusual call activity has not been documented. There is a reason for that. Directional call buying, with a constant diet, is a "mug's game" and results in losses for over 90% of traders. Its that simple, Pat .
I have read this study and it is inconclusive. Moreover it touches on other variables.
Charts and fundamentals - not constellations, sunspots, "feels" or 'unusual call activity' - represent legitimate methods of trading and investing.

This "unusual call activity" is about the lamest crap imaginable. The refusal to document win/loss rates and the overwhelming academic evidence are testimony to the nonsense that is presented as a bonafide trading angle/method. @realmoney
